His state recently equipped 500 cars with tachographs to test a mile payment system.
“ This is the best alternative in the long run, ” he said.
Bureaucrats call it a mile based user fee.
Not surprisingly, urban liberals like the idea, because the tax could be used, for example, to influence driving behaviour in such a way as to reduce congestion and climate-damaging exhaust gases.
