In New York City, transport officials want to develop a tax device that can also pay parking fees, have to be paid only for kilometres kilometres, and speed data to be collected in real time from other vehicles that allow drivers to avoid congestion.
“ Drivers are motivated to participate by the added value of the benefits offered by the system, ” says a city planning document.
Some traffic planners, however, wonder whether all the talk of paying per mile is not just a huge distraction.
Officials at the Metropolitan Transportation Commission for San Francisco Bay declared that Congress could solve the problem of the bankrupt Highway Trust Fund simply by raising the fuel tax.
An additional one-time fee or an annual levy could be imposed on drivers with hybrid vehicles or other vehicles that consume little petrol, so that they also pay a fair share.
