“ We are very hopeful that this type of vaccination strategy can help once millions of smokers who have tried to stop it, trying out all the methods available on the market, but have seen that their nicotine addiction is stronger than these approaches, ” Cornell says.
The new vaccine contains a harmless virus that has been modified to contain genetic information to produce nicotine antibodies.
The virus selectively infects the liver ’ s cells, which then produce a constant stream of antibodies.
The antibodies hase the nicotine molecules in the blood and neutralize them before they reach the brain, so a smoker does not experience a nicotine high.
In experiments, vaccinated mice given to nicotine maintained its normal level of activity.
By contrast, mice without vaccination would have taken a “ break, ” researchers declared, a sign that nicotine had reached their brain.
The experiments are described in the Science Translational Medicine.
Previous tobacco vaccines failed because they contained antibodies.
Vaccinations had to be given so often to maintain the antibody level that they were expensive and impractical.
But the cost of the new vaccine is likely to be significantly lower, because it transforms liver cells into antibody factories.
As Professor Crystal said, a future vaccine for humans, if safe, could be administered to children before they were tempted to try a cigarette, thereby preventing nicotine addiction.
It is more likely, however, that smokers would use it to stop.
“ They then know that when they start smoking again, they no longer feel a pleasure because of the nicotine vaccine, and that helps them to remove their habit, ” he explains.
