Professor Georgio Vallortigara, a neuroscientist at the University of Trento, said: “ Humans are well aware that the left and right halves of the brain react differently to stimuli that arouse positive or negative emotions. ”
Here we have tried to look at other species.
He also noted that in dogs, as in humans, the right half of the brain is responsible for the movement of the left, and vice versa, and that the two hemisphes played different roles in feelings.
